The paper focuses on the security analysis of the control plane in SDNs, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the need for standardization of methodologies for automated security analysis, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and system and control theory (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the vulnerabilities of the controller software, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL).
